# Build the Reactions Bridge

> **Historical receipt only.** Joel rejected reactions as an operator action system on 2026-07-19. Do not follow the imperative reaction instructions below. New work starts at [Button-native Telegram interactions](./design-button-native-interactions.svx).

## Step

Resolved when a reaction (or short reply) on an outbound message
reaches the owning consumer as an event with the original message's
correlation id — and the first customer works end to end: reacting to
a neat-memory DM writes the `outcome` grade into
`~/.joelclaw/observer-neat-memories.json`, feeding the
[reactions-teach-taste loop](../recall-consumption/build-neat-memory-dm.svx).

## Answer (2026-07-17)

Built two host-worker functions: `message/reaction-bridge` correlates the
nested observe-only inbound reaction through the contract Redis index, the
legacy Telegram flow index, or the durable message journal; then it emits the
transition-safe `message/reaction.received` contract. The
`message/neat-memory-reaction-grade` consumer accepts only Joel-authorized
added reactions, maps `👍 ❤️ 🔥 💯` to `worked` and `👎 💩` to
`did-not-work`, verifies `observer/neat-memory` ownership from the journal,
and atomically replaces the matching 0600 state file. Timestamp fallback is
limited to one unambiguous candidate inside two minutes; explicit flow/slug
matches win.

The return-path contract now explicitly accepts both `flow_v2_*` and the
legacy `notify:*` IDs that still exist on messages already sent during the
migration. The acting gateway and the bus bridge use the same deterministic
event identity, so an acting-path publication and a shadow-bridge publication
dedupe instead of grading twice. Notify compatibility now preserves its source
in the outbound correlation ID for future flow-v2 neat-memory rows. Per the
task stop rule, these gateway source changes were not activated with a gateway
restart.

Receipts:

- Root `bunx tsc --noEmit` — exit 0. Targeted system-bus, gateway, and
  message-contract typechecks also passed.
- Targeted Biome over the 40 relevant contract/gateway/system-bus files — no
  fixes required.
- Relevant suites — 78 passed, 0 failed, 182 expectations. The reaction tests
  execute the real nested event through `InngestTestEngine`, cover rejected
  actors, Redis and journal correlation, canonical and legacy envelopes,
  emoji mapping, legacy state migration, ambiguous matching, 0600 atomic
  replacement, and idempotence.
- Fresh-context review after fixes: clean enough for supervised registration
  and the real-event redrive.
- Supervised host-worker bounce only: PID `83853` → `43669`; live cwd remained
  `packages/system-bus`; `PUT /api/inngest` returned `Successfully registered`;
  health reported 152 functions with both new IDs. Gateway was not restarted.
- Real Telegram update `rawEventId=777932597`, platform message `14562`, was
  redriven without flattening its original nested payload. Inbound event
  `01KXQ4ET7TBCZAZCJA30QFT3EK` completed bridge run
  `01KXQ4ET8F334EAMM6RFXDA0HD` and correlated to legacy flow
  `notify:7c1924bc-b192-42da-b145-64dedfa2fe94`.
- That run emitted real `message/reaction.received` event
  `01KXQ4ETEFYRQ7069Q1RFD0F98`. Grade run
  `01KXQ4ETGFXZEKE547W7PVAHZD` completed and correctly ignored `👏` as
  `emoji-unmapped`; the state file remained mode 0600 with no fabricated
  outcome.

Live taste-loop proof remains deliberately human-shaped: steering runs the real
curator beat with
`NEAT_MEMORY_TRIGGER=beat bash ~/.joelclaw/observer-release/bin/neat-memory.sh`.
If its receipt says `action: send`, Joel reacts to that exact DM with one of the
configured grade emoji. Then inspect the matching entry in
`~/.joelclaw/observer-neat-memories.json`; its `outcome` must change. Do not
send a fake `--source observer/neat-memory` canary.

**Live proof landed (2026-07-17).** Joel reacted to the real curator DM for
slug `2026-07-17-248a3715344a` (sent 04:18:53Z, score 9, useful-resurfacing);
the memory-system-review curation survey read the state file and found
`outcome: "worked"` written by the grade consumer — a human thumbprint through
the full path: Telegram reaction → shadow tap → `message/inbound.reaction` →
bridge → `message/reaction.received` → grade → atomic 0600 state write. The
survey also quoted `judgePrompt` proving outcomes feed `{{history}}` on the
next beat: grades are consumed, not just recorded.

## Superseded interaction model — 2026-07-19

This remains a truthful historical receipt, but reactions are no longer an accepted operator-action surface. New actionable DMs use labeled inline buttons and publish `message/action.requested`; callbacks must not synthesize emoji or reuse `message/reaction.received`. See [Button-native Telegram interactions](./design-button-native-interactions.svx) and the [Campaign Pulse reaction retirement proposal](./proposal-retire-campaign-pulse-reactions.svx).
